        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Windows'); ?>
        <p><strong>Microsoft Windows</strong> is a series of graphical interface operating systems developed, marketed, and sold by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Microsoft introduced an operating environment named Windows on 20 November 1985 as a graphical operating system shell for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MS-DOS', 'DOS'); ?> in response to the growing interest in <strong>Graphical User Interfaces</strong> (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('GUI', 'IT'); ?>).</p>
        <p>Microsoft Windows came to dominate the world's personal computer market with over 90% market share, overtaking <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac OS', 'OS'); ?>, which had been introduced in 1984.</p>
        <p>The history of Windows dates back to September 1981, when <strong>Chase Bishop</strong>, designed the first model of an electronic device and project "<em>Interface Manager</em>" was started.</p>
